  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help 301 Refugee Children In Burundi Get Education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugee children we assist are victims of armed conflicts and other kind of violence in the eastern Democratic Republic of Congo. When they survive their families flee to neighboring countries like Burundi and are unable to meet their basic needs, including education. The AMV since 2006 has set up an Emergency Education structure in Bujumbura, which benefit more than 200 children each year. The AMV mission is to provide quality Education to refugee kids in order to overcome future challenges.</narrative>
  </description>
